cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new module for semantic segmentation, which involves learning to re-weight local features through guidance from pixel-wise semantic prediction. This involves a learning process, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with scene parsing, which involves natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
